cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.SD, cs.CL, cs.SOC

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper investigates the dynamics of emotional chats within a social network of interacting agents. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is also likely as the paper explores the role of emotions in human dynamics online. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the design and implementation of emotional Bots. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also less likely but possible as the paper uses machine-learning methods for extracting emotion components from text messages. 
- cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) is also possible as the paper investigates collective behavior induced by emotional chats with Bots.
